The paper deals with Constraint Satisfaction Problems (CSPs), which are a fundamental topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The focus is on CSPs of bounded width, which are closely related to the study of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a new consistency notion, which is a concept in Logic and Computation (cs.LO), and discusses its computational advantages, which are relevant to Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
